9: 7-12. We </div><div class="t m35a x64 h2d y184e ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">know that it is the.eternal Spirit. Heb. 9 : 14. We know </div><div class="t m5eb x61 h2d y28a ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">that it is the Comforter (John 14 : 26), and the Spirit of </div><div class="t mf0 x61 h2d y182a ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">truth (John 15: 26). These names are given because </div><div class="t m180 x61 h2d y16b6 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">there is comfort in the truth. It is of much more im-</div><div class="t m1cc x61 h2d y24d ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">portance to us that we receive the Spirit than that we try </div><div class="t mb18 x61 h2d y1923 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">to discern what it is. &quot; Holy Ghost &quot; and &quot; Holy Spirit &quot; </div><div class="t m73f x61 h2d y17f9 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">are from the same original words, and seem to be used </div><div class="t m76e x61 h2d y41f ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">interchangeably in the King James&apos; Version. The Amer-</div><div class="t m3f2 x61 h2d yc60 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">ican members of the Revision Committee desired to use </div><div class="t m771 x61 h2d y1aa5 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">in all cases the term &quot; Holy Spirit.&quot; </div><div class="t m127 x60 h2d y1982 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">2. </div><div class="t mdb7 x65 h2d y17d9 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">FAITH in Christ makes us children of God (Gal. 3 : </div><div class="t md13 x61 h2d yfa6 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">26), and the Spirit is given because we are sons (Gal. 4: </div><div class="t m672 x61 h2d y691 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">6) ; ,and so Paul asked the believers if they had received </div><div class="t m1c9 x61 h2d y1902 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the Holy Spirit (Acts 19 : 2). All things are ours (1 Cor. </div><div class="t mcdb x61 h2d y1cc2 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">3: 22), but God does not give spiritual blessings against </div><div class="t m7e9 x61 h2d y1cc3 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">our will, and so we are to ask (Matt. 7 : 7) for the Spirit, </div><div class="t mb42 x61 h2d y1719 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">with the assurance that he will give willingly (Luke 11: </div><div class="t m34b x61 h2d y6b6 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">13&apos;. This the disciples did (Acts 1 : 5, 14), and their re-</div><div class="t mea4 x61 h2d y1a60 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">quest was granted (Acts 2 : 4). The promise that was ful-</div><div class="t ma1e x61 h2d y161f ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">filled to them (Joel 2 : 28, 29) is for us also. The posses-</div><div class="t m764 x61 h2d y1926 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">sion of the Spirit irdicah</div><div class="t mbf5 x77 h2d y91f ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">,</div><div class="t mab7 x9e h2d y1ae8 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">s a union with God (1 John 3: </div><div class="t m1892 x61 h2d y32b ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">24; 4 : 13),</div><div class="t m1bc8 xb8 h2d y32b ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">,</div><div class="t m567 xd h2d y19f0 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">and no one can be Christ&apos;s without it (Rom. 8: </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
